	Math-Brent, version 1.00, 26 December 2015

An implementation of Brent's method for one-dimensional minimisation
of a function without using derivatives, and an implementation of the
Van Wijngaarden-Dekker-Brent Method, used to find a function's root.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Math::Brent

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Math-Brent

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Math-Brent

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Math-Brent

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Math-Brent/


